{"calories":"690","carbs":91,"category":{"badge_name":"","display_name":"Dinner","display_order":1,"is_filterable":false,"insight_segment_slug":"main-recipe-ratings","slug":"main"},"choices_available":[],"description":"\u003cp\u003eEvery year for Hanukkah, Chef Michelle’s family makes latkes with all the fixings, a tradition she’s brought to the Plated Test Kitchen. In this repeat-favorite, celebration-worthy recipe, grated potato is combined with egg and flour, then flattened and fried until crispy outside and tender inside. We’ve added some refined accoutrements in the form of tangy horseradish-infused sour cream, roasted carrots, and a spinach salad laced with mustardy dressing. The only thing more fun than making these? Eating them!\u003c/p\u003e","difficulty":"medium","external_id":"297bc1357b","fat":30,"images":[{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35485/large_cropped_KUxp5BuMTCyBWLM26zJx_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cre_me_Frai_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_0508___MAIN.jpg","size":"large_cropped","type":"main_cropped"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35492/1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"full","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35492/hero_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"hero","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35492/menu_small_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"medium-rectangle","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35492/small_square_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"small-square","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35492/medium_square_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"medium-square","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35492/recipe_profile_page_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"large-rectangle","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35490/1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_THUMB.jpg","size":"full","type":"card"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35490/menu_small_1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_THUMB.jpg","size":"medium-rectangle","type":"card"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35491/1876_Potato_Latkes_with_Horseradish_Cr_me_Fra_che__Roasted_Carrots__and_Spinach_Salad_MOBILE.jpg","size":"full","type":"portrait"}}],"name":"Potato Latkes with Horseradish Sour Cream, Roasted Carrots, and Spinach Salad","novice_time":"","portion_count":2,"prep_time":"40-50","pro_time":"","product_type":{"slug":"subscription","included_in_subscription":true},"protein":16,"public_slug":"potato-latkes-with-horseradish-creme-fraiche-roasted-carrots-and-spinach-salad-4","pdf_url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/public_uploads/recipe/region_schedule/downloadable_recipe_card/20858/recipe_card20171130-4-14kup6.pdf","recipe_id":3557,"type":"regular","servings":2,"short_name":"Potato Latkes","subtitle":"with Horseradish Sour Cream, Roasted Carrots, and Spinach Salad","title":"Potato Latkes","legal_copy_short":null,"available_for_non_sub":false,"additional_price":"0","cooking_tip":"\u003cp\u003eBe sure to read through the entire recipe before you begin cooking. Trust us—you'll be glad you did! \u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you have an eager helper, enlist them to grate potatoes while you prep the rest of the ingredients!\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe secret to perfectly browned and crispy latkes is drying the potatoes as much as possible. Be sure to wring out any excess moisture before frying. Repeat if necessary with a fresh towel.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eUse enough canola oil to reach about .5-inch up the sides of the pan or halfway up the latkes.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e","equipment":["box grater","baking sheet","12\" large nonstick pan"],"id":3557,"ingredients":["baby spinach","russet potatoes","baby carrots","chives","shallot","flour","Champagne vinegar","Dijon mustard","nonfat sour cream","horseradish"],"ingredients_full":[{"name":"baby spinach","quantity":"5.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":1,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/7/medium_square_spinach-2.jpg"},{"name":"russet potatoes","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":2,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/438/medium_square_idaho-potato.jpg"},{"name":"baby carrots","quantity":"6.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1372/medium_square_carrots__baby_peeled.jpg"},{"name":"chives","quantity":"0.125","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":4,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1281/medium_square_medium_square_chives-2-test.jpg"},{"name":"shallot","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":5,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/130/medium_square_SHALLOT_copy.jpg"},{"name":"flour","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":6,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/285/medium_square_FLOUR_copy.jpg"},{"name":"Champagne vinegar","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":7,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/252/medium_square_vinegar-champagne-2.jpg"},{"name":"Dijon mustard","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"packet","displayOrder":8,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/37/medium_square_dijon-test.jpg"},{"name":"nonfat sour cream","quantity":"4.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":9,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2062/medium_square_sour-cream-1.jpg"},{"name":"horseradish","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/255/medium_square_HORSERADISH001.jpg"}],"is_tastemaker":false,"upgradeable":false,"is_holiday_hack":false,"pantry_items":[],"pantry_items_full":[],"steps":[{"title":"Prepare Ingredients","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35494/recipe_card_size_1._Prepare_Ingredients.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003ePreheat oven to 425°F. Rinse all produce. Pat \u003cstrong\u003espinach \u003c/strong\u003edry with paper towel. Grate \u003cstrong\u003epotatoes\u003c/strong\u003e on the large holes of a box grater (see Recipe Tip), then place in a strainer over a medium bowl to drain. Halve \u003cstrong\u003ecarrots \u003c/strong\u003elengthwise. Thinly slice \u003cstrong\u003echives\u003c/strong\u003e. Peel \u003cstrong\u003eshallot\u003c/strong\u003e and thinly slice into rings.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Roast Vegetables","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35493/recipe_card_size_2._Roast_Vegetables.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eOn a baking sheet, toss \u003cstrong\u003ecarrots\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003epepper \u003c/strong\u003eas desired. Roast until starting to become tender, about 10 minutes. Then, add \u003cstrong\u003eshallot\u003c/strong\u003e to baking sheet, toss to combine, and return to oven. Roast until carrots are completely tender and shallot is caramelized, 10 minutes more. \u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Make Latke Mixture","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35488/recipe_card_size_3._Make_Latke_Mixture.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile vegetables roast, press \u003cstrong\u003egrated potatoes\u003c/strong\u003e down in strainer to remove excess moisture. Then, wrap \u003cstrong\u003epotatoes\u003c/strong\u003e in a clean kitchen towel or paper towels and squeeze to wring out as much water as possible (see Recipe Tip). Transfer \u003cstrong\u003epotatoes\u003c/strong\u003e to a large bowl and add \u003cstrong\u003eflour\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e1 egg\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e1 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003epepper \u003c/strong\u003eas desired. Using your hands, mix well to fully combine.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Fry Latkes","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35487/recipe_card_size_4._Fry_Latkes.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eHeat\u003cstrong\u003e canola oil\u003c/strong\u003e (see Recipe Tip) in a large nonstick pan over medium-high heat. When oil is shimmering, gently add \u003cstrong\u003e.25 cup latke mixture\u003c/strong\u003e at a time. Flatten each \u003cstrong\u003elatke\u003c/strong\u003e slightly with a spatula and fry, working in batches and adding more canola oil as needed, until golden and crisp, about 4 minutes per side. Using a slotted spoon or tongs, transfer \u003cstrong\u003elatkes\u003c/strong\u003e to a paper towel-lined plate to drain. Sprinkle over \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e. Set aside. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Make Vinaigrette","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35489/recipe_card_size_5._Make_Dressing.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eIn a large bowl, whisk together \u003cstrong\u003eChampagne vinegar\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of mustard \u003c/strong\u003euntil smooth. Discard remaining mustard, or save for a sandwich. Whisking continuously, slowly add \u003cstrong\u003e2 tablespoons olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e until fully combined. Season \u003cstrong\u003evinaigrette\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e and\u003cstrong\u003e pepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Set aside.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Finish and Plate Latkes","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/35486/recipe_card_size_6._Plate_Latkes_and_Salad.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eIn a medium bowl, stir together \u003cstrong\u003esour cream\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003ehorseradish\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of chives\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003esalt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Add \u003cstrong\u003espinach\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003eroasted\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003evegetables\u003c/strong\u003e to bowl with vinaigrette and toss to coat. Serve \u003cstrong\u003epotato latkes\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003espinach salad\u003c/strong\u003e and garnish with \u003cstrong\u003eremaining chives\u003c/strong\u003e. Dollop over \u003cstrong\u003ehorseradish sour cream\u003c/strong\u003e for maximum deliciousness.\u003c/p\u003e"}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""}],"allergens":[{"name":"Egg","slug":"egg","hex_color":""},{"name":"Milk","slug":"milk","hex_color":""},{"name":"Wheat","slug":"wheat","hex_color":""}],"proteins":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"Vegetable","slug":"vegetable","hex_color":""}],"publicFacing":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""}],"feature":[]}}